""text"":""After making use of one of the Void Seeds I obtained via closing a rift and taking advantage of the permeability quartz seems to have with vis, as well as taking a porous physical object like a sponge, I was able to create an object that I'm surprised is even able to exist at all. Quite frankly I wasn't all too confident this would work considering how haphazardly I threw together all the components for this ‚Äúflux sponge‚Äù as I'll call it. It seems to absorb all the flux in an area with seemingly no cost, and can even wipe away flux rifts entirely! I'm not sure where any of the flux goes, but the voices in my head tell me not to worry about it. So I suppose that's that!
As a side note, it appears if I use this flux sponge, I don't see any of the usual benefits of closing a rift. Since I don't seem to acquire any void seeds or the occasional primordial pearl."",
